h3. *Summary*
Usual CURL command to download .zip files in a repository isn&#x27;t seem to be working.

h3. *How to reproduce*
# Upload a .zip file in your repository Downloads tab
# Download the .zip file using the below commands (with App Password authentication)

{code}
#!CURL

curl -u username:app_password -L -O https://bitbucket.org/username/repository_name/downloads/zip_file_name.zip
{code}

h3. *Expected Results*
Will be able to download ".zip" file contents.

h3. *Actual Results*
The downloaded ".zip" file contents is not download.\\
The ".zip" file is 0 bytes size.

h3. *Workaround*
Use the below CURL command by replacing the URL to an API endpoint format

{code}
#!CURL

curl -u username:app_password -L -O https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/username/repository_username/downloads/zip_file_name.zip
{code}

